---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Contact"
  description="Contact the office of Lama Karma Dorje — teaching enquiries, media requests, retreat bookings, and general correspondence."
>

  <!-- ── Page Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-content">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">We welcome you</span>
      <h1>Contact</h1>
      <p>For teaching enquiries, retreat bookings, media requests, and correspondence with the office of Lama Karma Dorje.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Contact Body ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section" style="background:var(--color-bg);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="contact-grid">

        <!-- ── Left: Contact Info ─────────────────────── -->
        <aside>
          <span class="section-eyebrow">Get in Touch</span>
          <h2 style="font-size:clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem);color:var(--color-primary);margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            Office of Lama Karma Dorje
          </h2>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:2rem;">
            The office at Norbu Ling handles all correspondence on behalf of Lama Karma Dorje. Please allow 5–10 working days for a response. During retreat periods, response times may be longer.
          </p>

          <div class="contact-info-block">
            <!-- Address -->
            <div class="contact-info-item">
              <div class="contact-icon">
                <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0 1 18 0z"/>
                  <circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>Address</h4>
                <p>Norbu Ling Retreat Centre<br />Bir Tibetan Colony<br />Bir, Himachal Pradesh 176077<br />India</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Email -->
            <div class="contact-info-item">
              <div class="contact-icon">
                <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/>
                  <polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>Email</h4>
                <a href="mailto:office@lamakarmadorje.org">office@lamakarmadorje.org</a>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Office Hours -->
            <div class="contact-info-item">
              <div class="contact-icon">
                <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                  <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
                  <polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4>Office Hours</h4>
                <p>Monday – Friday<br />9:00 am – 4:00 pm IST<br />(UTC +5:30)</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Notices -->
          <div style="margin-top:2.5rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">
            <div class="notice-box">
              <strong>Media Enquiries</strong><br />
              Journalists, filmmakers, and researchers wishing to interview or film Lama Karma Dorje should write to the office with a detailed proposal and their institutional affiliation. We aim to respond within two weeks.
            </div>
            <div class="notice-box">
              <strong>Teaching Invitations</strong><br />
              Dharma centres wishing to invite Lama Karma Dorje to teach should submit a formal invitation letter through email, including proposed dates, topic, and expected audience. Invitations are reviewed annually each January.
            </div>
            <div class="notice-box">
              <strong>Personal Meetings</strong><br />
              Students who have attended at least one teaching may request a personal meeting. Requests should be made through the office. Meetings are offered in a spirit of genuine practice guidance, not casual consultation.
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <!-- ── Right: Contact Form ─────────────────── -->
        <div>
          <div style="background:var(--color-bg-card);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:12px;padding:2.5rem;">
            <h3 style="font-size:1.5rem;color:var(--color-primary);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Send a Message</h3>
            <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--color-text-muted);margin-bottom:2rem;">
              The best way to reach the Norbu Ling office is by email. We aim to respond within 5–10 working days.
            </p>
            <a href="mailto:office@lamakarmadorje.org" class="btn btn--primary" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/>
                <polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/>
              </svg>
              office@lamakarmadorje.org
            </a>
            <div style="margin-top:2rem;padding:1rem;background:var(--color-bg-warm);border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--color-border);font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.65;">
              <strong style="color:var(--color-text);display:block;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Response Times</strong>
              We respond to all enquiries within 5–10 working days. During retreat periods response times may be longer. Teaching invitations are reviewed annually each January.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── How to Find Norbu Ling ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section--sm" style="background:var(--color-bg-warm);">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px;">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-eyebrow">Getting Here</span>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;color:var(--color-primary);margin-bottom:1rem;">How to Reach Norbu Ling</h2>
      </div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="travel-grid">
        <div class="notice-box">
          <strong>By Air</strong><br />
          The nearest airport is Dharamsala (Gaggal) Airport (DHM), approximately 70 km from Bir. Flights operate from Delhi (DEL) and Chandigarh (IXC). From Dharamsala, taxis to Bir take approximately 2 hours.
        </div>
        <div class="notice-box">
          <strong>By Train</strong><br />
          The nearest railhead is Pathankot Junction (PTK), served by trains from Delhi, Mumbai, and Amritsar. From Pathankot, shared taxis and buses operate to Bir (approximately 3 hours).
        </div>
        <div class="notice-box">
          <strong>By Road</strong><br />
          Bir is located on the NH-154A. From Delhi, the drive takes approximately 10–12 hours via Chandigarh and Mandi. HRTC Volvo buses operate overnight from Delhi's ISBT Kashmiri Gate to Baijnath (5 km from Bir).
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .travel-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr) !important;
    }
  }
</style>
